Enumeration Type Documentation

enum EncodingType
 

DODS understands two types of encoding: x-plain and deflate, which correspond to plain uncompressed data and data compressed with zlib's LZW algorithm respectively.

{verbatim} enum EncodingType { unknown_enc, deflate, x_plain }; {verbatim}

The type of encoding used on the current stream.
